        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>8&#47;18&#47;88<lb/>
                My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have arranged<lb/> for you to lecture next Sunday<lb/> at 11.30 for 12.  Dr Adler will com&#45;<lb/>mence about 10.30&#45;say 10.45.<lb/></p>
            <p>This will enable you to<lb/> be present at the meeting in Brooklyn<lb/> at 3 or 3.30.  And I hope for you to get home<lb/> in decent time.<lb/></p>
            <p>But do you think it advisable<lb/> for all three of us to be present at the<lb/> meeting&#44; you&#44; I and Dr Drachman.<lb/>  Dr D. thinks it hardly the thing.  But if we<lb/> can capture the place and abolish<lb/> the pews&#44; no trouble will be too great.<lb/>  If you think two will be sufficient<lb/> I will stay away&#44; especially as I<lb/> have a wedding in this city at 5.30 or<lb/> 6 p. m.&#45;&#45;Friedlander will call<lb/> for us at 2.30. or 2 p. m.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>he seems to have been working hard<lb/> and in trying to get a new building&#44;&#45;&#45;<lb/> the present is unfitted&#44; in a bad<lb/> position&#44;&#45;&#45;they need a new building and<lb/> the present by reason of its inferior gallery<lb/> accommodations is not much fitted<lb/> for separation of the sexes&#58;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>he has stopped then appropriating money<lb/> for repairs&#44; and has been canvassing for<lb/> a new structure&#44;&#45;&#45;but Sunday the<lb/> bad questions will be discovered.&#45;&#45;<lb/> a new synagogue and abolition of<lb/> pews.<lb/></p>
            <p>Should you lecture next Sunday<lb/> morning&#44;&#45;&#45;i. e. should nothing occur to<lb/> keep you&#45;&#45;I suggest that you make it<lb/> say 50 minutes&#45;&#45;and then let the audience<lb/> disperse before 1 p. m. dinner hour.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yrs with regard to all<lb/>
                H Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
            </body>
